
Here's a .gitignore configuration that ignores common Python project clutter:

# Compiled Python files
__pycache__/

# Distribution / packaging
dist/
build/
develop-eggs/
eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg

# IDE and virtualenv settings
.idea/
.vscode/
.venv/

# Unit test / coverage reports
.tox/
.coverage
.cache
nosetests.xml
coverage.xml

# IDE stuff (adjust based on your IDE)
*.pydevproject
*.project

# Sphinx documentation
docs/_build/
